 must be updated for the Lucene 6 API.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. If porting or regenerating tests around org.apache.lucene.util.AttributeImpl, note that Lucene 6.0.0 makes reflectWith(AttributeReflector) abstract; every custom AttributeImpl subclass must import org.apache.lucene.util.AttributeReflector and implement reflectWith, e.g. by calling reflector.reflect(TheAttribute.class, \\\"fieldName\\\", value). Meaningful coverage can be reached using lucene-core APIs only: index/search/store/util classes, custom Analyzer/TokenStream fixtures, in-memory or temporary Directory usage, and bundled SPI resources/codecs.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Common Lucene examples often use analyzers from lucene-analyzers-common, but that is not required for lucene-core coverage and should not be added unless the generated test deliberately depends on analyzer-module classes.\",\n    \"The compile failure is an API-compatibility issue in test code, not evidence of a missing external dependency or service.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d70ba9977844968016a3f98d9b3a081978e534355ba230a6c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 725, "output": 797, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34802, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782552781975, "responseId": "resp_0d70ba9977844968016a3f98ce9f448197b4d9c7abc53ed2fa"}, "toolResults": []}
